  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">WASH responses to vulnerable out-of-camp South Sudanese Refugees in Naivasha settlement in Khartoum</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This project aims at supporting vulnerable out-of-camp South Sudanese Refugees (SSRs)  by providing sanitation and hygiene services, including school WASH facility provision in Naivasha settlement (Khartoum Open areas) in Omdurman locality, Khartoum state. 
Main project activities:
-Construction of 60 shared family latrines with adjacent 60 showers
-Undertaking of garbage collection and disposal campaigns (two campaigns per month)
-Assigning of community hygiene promoters (CHPs) to deliver day to day awareness raising to their community  through distributing IEC materials, conduct mass awareness campaign, distributing hygiene kits, organize hygiene celebration and events- the CHPs will run their job from the clinics
-Undertake two 3-day workshop trainings on hygiene promotion for 60 CHPs drawn from Nifasha camp to enable them address hygiene issues towards changing behaviour practices
-Undertaking of a one 3-day trainings of 30 members of two primary school PTAs on maintenance and operation of WASH facilities
-Undertaking of a one 5-day CHAST trainings for 30 students drown from two schools to support in establishment of  hygiene clubs in two primary schools to undertaking regular safe sanitation and hygiene practices
-Undertaking of 1 drama and video session on quarterly basis including celebration of GHWD to be conducted at schools
-Provision of hygiene kits (dignity kit, Ibrik, Soap, Potties) as in-kind items to the needy target families</narrative>
  </description>
